cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with interpolation for the theory of arrays, which is a logical theory. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper mentions using the algorithm to prove memory safety for C programs. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with arrays, which are a common data structure. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper mentions the usefulness of the produced interpolants for proving memory safety in C programs, which is a software engineering concern. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the quantifier-free fragment of the theory of arrays, which can be seen as a formal language.
